<html
  xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
  xmlns:tal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/tal"
  xmlns:metal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/metal"
  xmlns:i18n="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/i18n"
  xml:lang="en"
  lang="en"
  dir="ltr"
  metal:use-macro="context/@@main_template/master"
  i18n:domain="launchpad"
>

<body>

<div metal:fill-slot="main">

  <div metal:use-macro="context/@@launchpad_form/form">

    <p metal:fill-slot="extra_info" style="background: #e0f0d0; padding: 0.5em">
      Before you register a project from scratch, you might want to search
      through the
      <a href="/projects">existing projects registered in Launchpad</a>
      and see if the
      project you are thinking of is not already in there. If so, you can
      just <a href="/launchpad/+addquestion">ask our staff</a> to make
      that project part of your project group.
    </p>

  </div>

</div>
</body>
</html>

